    "en": {
      "title": "Monday declared as National Dengue Eradication Day",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "As the risk of dengue fever is increasing across the country, the day after tomorrow, Monday, has been declared as National Dengue Eradication Day, Director of Health Services, Special Medical Specialist Asela Gunawardena said.",
        "So far this year, 43,000 people have been infected with dengue fever throughout the country. The director of health services also mentioned that up to Friday, 22nd of this month, about 8,000 people have contracted dengue fever.",
        "He further mentioned that government and private institutions, schools, construction sites, factories and other public places have been identified as areas with dangerous environment where dengue fever spreads.",
        "As the day after tomorrow has been declared as National Dengue Eradication Day, the Director of Health Services appealed to the general public to spare at least one hour for cleaning their workplaces and the environment of their homes on that day."
      ],
